result.execSummary:
The defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jammie D Sanderfoot is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jammie D Sanderfoot was found guilty of Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.
  • Jammie D Sanderfoot was found guilty of Intent. Contribute/Delinquency Child [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.40(1).
  • Jammie D Sanderfoot was found guilty of Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot in custody.   Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:08 PM. State - resolved - has complied with victim notification requirement and has filed the restitution report and order. Scholke - amend count #1 to criminal trespassing contrary to 943.014 deleting repeater allegation but PTAC, plead to counts #2 and #4 as alleged, dismiss count #3; joint recommendation of 9 months incarceration on each count - concurrent to each other and concurrent to current sentence that the defendant is serving, costs, restitution of $357.11 (includes VW Surcharge). State agrees and gives breakdown of restitution as it is stated on restitution report and order. Court amends count #1 criminal trespassing to a dwelling contrary to 943.014 with no repeater allegation, all counts will have the repeater allegation dismissed. Court dismisses count #3. Sanderfoot pleads G to count #1 as amended, count #2 as alleged. Court amends count #4 to delete repeater allegation. Sanderfoot pleads G to count #4 as amended. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea, right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Scholke makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Sanderfoot makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: all counts (#1, #2 and #4) - 9 months in FC jail - concurrent to each other and to sentence that the defendant is now serving, costs on each count - to be paid with 25% of his prison wages/funds available to him, restitution including  VW surcharge totalling $357.11 - paid same as costs, submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.
Plea/sentencing hearing on May 13, 2016 at 01:00 pm.
Jury trial on May 13, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot, in custody in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Charles Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:48 PM. Scholke - not resolved - has gone over Frye with the defendant. Court continues bond, sets for JT. State - agreement was as follows: G to count #1 as alleged, G to count #2 as alleged, #3 and #4 - DRI, 5 years probation on counts #1 and #2 with 1 year conditional jail time, tweeked offer recently of removing repeater compoments with 180 days jail for stated reasons. Court sets for JT.  Jury trial scheduled for May 13, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot in custody and appears via video from FOSO.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:48 PM. State - believes it will be a waiver of PH and has filed an Information that mirrors complaint in anticipation of that. Scholke and Sanderfoot agree. Court has waiver of PH form, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. Scholke has Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and pleads NG to all counts. Court accepts plea, continues bond (defendant is currently on a hold) and sets for FPT.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 9, 2016 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot in court with attorney Michael Scholke.  Defendant Jammie D Sanderfoot in custody and appears via video from FOSO.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 9:38 AM. Sanderfoot has complaint as does Scholke, waives reading of it, requests PH. State - bond - requests bond remain the same ($2,000.00 cash). Scholke - no objection - would like PH within 10 days. Court continues bond, sets for PH.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for January 28, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
